Cross sections for  the  reactions  Li-7(gamma,n0+n2)
and  Li-7(gamma,p0)  have  been  measured for photon
energies in the range 60-120 MeV. Comparison is made
between  the  data  and simple calculations based on
the modified quasideuteron  and  quasifree  knockout
models, which suggests that the former dominates.
